<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-316-143  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 316 143.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  Feb 7 1989 v3 n6 p5(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VideoShow, PhotoMetric for Mac ship. (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Guglielmo, Connie.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   General Parametrics Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   General Parametrics VideoShow Professional (Computer apparatus)(product introduction)General Parametrics Videoshow Executive (Computer apparatus)(product introduction)General Parametrics Videoshow Companion (Computer apparatus)(product introduction)StarTime (Computer program) (product introduction)General Parametrics Natural Image Pack (Turnkey system) (productintroduction)PrintMaker (Computer program) (product introduction)General Parametrics PhotoMetric (Computer appartus) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Presentation HardwarePresentation SoftwareProduct IntroductionStand-Alone SystemsCompatible HardwareTurnkey Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VideoShow, PhotoMetric for Mac shipandM;BERKELEY, Calif.andP;  -- General Parametrics Corp. last month shipped Macintoshversions of its VideoShow portable presentations systems, PhotoMetric 35mmslide maker and presentation software.andM;VideoShow Professional, priced at $8,495, and the $2,695 VideoShow Executiveare stand-alone devices that display Mac-generated presentations and imagesmuch in the way slide projectors display 35mm slides.andP;  They hook up to colormonitors or video-projection systems and are operated via a remotecontroller.andP;  In addition to moving back and forth among images, thecontroller allows users to move an electronic pointer on the screen, overlayimages and highlight text.andM;VideoShow Professional displays images with up to 100,000 colors, whileExecutive offers up to 1,000 colors.andM;General Parametrics also plans to release in March a low-cost system calledVideoShow Companion.andP;  The $1,795 system, with a Mac, colorizesblack-and-white images and projects them with up to 1,000 colors on RGBmonitors.andM;The VideoShow systems display images created with any Mac software.andP;  The Macfile must be converted into VideoShow's format using a conversion and filecompression utility supplied by General Parametrics.andM;Presentations can also be created using Star-Time, a $199 program forediting, colorizing and sorting Mac-generated images.andP;  It offers suchtransitions as wipes and fades.andM;Natural Image Pak for Mac is designed for use with VideoShow Professional.andO;The $6,595 package consists of Truevision's NuVista frame grabber board forthe Mac II and General Parametrics' ImageProcessor software.andP;  Together, thetwo products let users capture, position, crop and compress live videoimages.andP;  Image-Processor is also sold separately for $1,995.andM;Two other products were released for use with the VideoShow systems:andM;* The $4,495 PhotoMetric slide maker produces 4,000-line resolution color35mm slides.andM;* PrintMaker, a $199 software package, lets users output VideoShowpresentations in color to a CalComp 5902G thermal printer or to theHewlett-Packard LaserJet Plus and LaserJet II printers.andM;General Parametrics Corp. is at 1250 Ninth St., Berkeley, Calif.andP;  94710;(415) 524-3950.andO;</TEXT></DOC>